TIMIT: Another speech modeling dataset is TIMIT with 6300 English sentences read by 630 speakers. Like the work done in (Fraccaro et al., 2016), our model is trained on raw sequences of 200 dimensional frames. In our experiments, we use 1024 hidden units, 2048 LSTM units and 128 latent variables, and batch size of 128. We train the model using learning rate of 0.0001,  = 1 and  = 0. The average log-likelihood for the sequences on test can be found in Table 1.
